Registry_approve
└── When reserve exists
    ├── When caller is owner
    │   ├── Given account is not isolated
    │   │   └── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.
    │   ├── Given account is isolated
    │   │   └── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.
    │   ├── When approving different token types
    │   │   └── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.
    │   └── When approving zero amount
    │       └── It should allow the approval transaction.
    ├── When caller is operator
    │   └── Given account is isolated
    │       ├── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.
    │       └── It shouldn't change the allowance amount returned by `allowance` for the owner.
    ├── When caller is unauthorized
    │   └── Given account is isolated
    │       ├── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.
    │       └── It shouldn't change the allowance amount returned by `allowance` for the owner.
    ├── When spender account is an isolated account // Doesn't matter who is the caller.
    │   └── It should revert.
    │       └── With `Registry__InvalidSpender` error.
    └── When reserve does not exist
        └── When caller is owner
            └── Given account is not isolated
                └── It should approve the other address to spend tokens.